elf agrandizing (my apologies to the pinesol troll) drivel.   In some of these cases the poster goes as far as pointing out their obvious hubris and either mocks themselves or says &quot;I'm cool, I deserve to be Hubretic.&quot;<br><br>Ok so the point you were asking about:<br><br>&quot;I think that many of the posts here are silly even the ones that I and other members of Wisdom have made.&quot;<br><br>Wow. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Silly does not equal Evil.<br><br>The point itself was silly.<br><br>No the admins of this board were not in my mind as some hypocrtical beasts that needed to be slain. (I honestly didn't even notice that you had started the bathroom cleaner thread until someone else pointed  it out to me.)<br><br>No it was not meant as a troll.<br><br>No the point was not &quot;elitest making fun of everyone here.&quot;  It's the result of being bored at work and wanting to goof off by poking fun of ourselves and a few other silly posts.  <br><br>No it was not &quot;planned&quot; to spam the board.  That didn't happen until after the posts were moved from the offtopic section to the flame board and the &quot;spamming&quot; was just us having fun.<br><br>This has turned into too much of a drama and that is sad.<br><br>I tried to convey &quot;the point&quot; subtly.  I was trying to make &quot;the point&quot; w/o the use of vile football metaphors or being crude.  However, I have learned that vile and crude behavior is tolerated /and/ expected here, that is sad as well.<br><br>That being said, those people that know me will prolly be quite supprised to see me post more then 3 lines on ANY topic as I am not known as a drama king or a wordy person.  I recognize that we're all flawed humans here in this situation and RL circumstances may influence poor online behaviour.  With that in mind I thought about posti